---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Cullis — Zero-trust identity and audit for AI agents">
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero-container">
      <aside class="hero-marginalia reveal">
        <div class="scribble">CLLS-0001</div>
        <div class="folio">research preview · <em>pre-1.0</em></div>
        <div class="marginalia">
          Cryptographic infrastructure for artificial agents — identity,
          authorization, and tamper-evident audit across organizations
          that do not trust one another.
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="hero-main">
        <div class="eyebrow reveal">
          <span class="pulse-dot"></span>
          Agent Trust Fabric
        </div>

        <h1 class="hero-title reveal" data-delay="1">
          Zero-trust <em>identity</em><br />
          &amp; <em>audit</em> for<br />
          AI agents.
        </h1>

        <p class="hero-lead reveal" data-delay="2">
          Start air-gapped inside your organization. Scale to
          cross-company federation — without redeploy. Per-agent
          cryptographic identity, tamper-evident hash-chain audit,
          end-to-end encrypted messaging.
        </p>

        <div class="hero-actions reveal" data-delay="3">
          <a href="/architecture" class="btn btn-primary">Read the architecture</a>
          <a href="/download" class="btn btn-ghost">Download Connector</a>
        </div>

        <dl class="hero-stats reveal" data-delay="4">
          <div>
            <dt>Cryptography</dt>
            <dd>ECC · <em>P-256</em></dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>License</dt>
            <dd>FSL-1.1 / Apache-2.0</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Stage</dt>
            <dd><em>research preview</em></dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <!-- PREMISE -->
  <section class="prose-section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="eyebrow reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow-number">01</span>
        The premise
      </div>
      <h2 class="reveal" data-delay="1">
        Three questions — <em>who</em>, <em>what</em>,<br/>
        and <em>what actually happened</em>.
      </h2>
      <p class="reveal dropcap" data-delay="2">
        Artificial agents act on your behalf. They read, decide, move money,
        speak to systems owned by other companies. When something goes wrong
        — and it will — three questions matter.
        <em>Who was it?</em> Not the user who typed a prompt last week, the
        specific agent process, with a cryptographic proof.
        <em>What were they allowed to do?</em> Not by policy written in a PDF,
        by policy enforced at the boundary before the call landed.
        <em>What did they actually do?</em> Not what logs you can still find,
        an append-only chain that cannot be silently rewritten.
      </p>
      <p class="reveal" data-delay="3">
        Cullis answers those three questions with three components that run
        entirely on your infrastructure: a connector at the edge, an
        authority inside your organization, and — when you need to reach
        agents in other companies — a court that routes between trust
        domains without reading the mail.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <!-- COMPONENTS -->
  <section class="components-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="eyebrow reveal">
          <span class="eyebrow-number">02</span>
          Three components
        </div>
        <h2 class="reveal" data-delay="1">
          The <em>fabric</em>, named.
        </h2>
        <p class="section-lead reveal" data-delay="2">
          Three independent, deployable components. A single company
          runs two; a consortium adds the third.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="components-grid">
        <article class="component-card reveal" data-delay="1">
          <div class="cc-number">01</div>
          <div class="cc-label">Edge</div>
          <h3 class="cc-title">Cullis <em>Connector</em></h3>
          <p class="cc-body">
            A desktop application that admits any MCP client — Claude
            Desktop, Cursor, Cline — into the Cullis network. Runs on
            the end user's laptop.
          </p>
          <dl class="cc-spec">
            <dt>Runs on</dt><dd>macOS · Windows · Linux</dd>
            <dt>Owned by</dt><dd>the end user</dd>
            <dt>Does</dt><dd>identity · MCP↔Cullis translation</dd>
          </dl>
        </article>

        <article class="component-card reveal" data-delay="2">
          <div class="cc-number">02</div>
          <div class="cc-label">Intra-org</div>
          <h3 class="cc-title">Cullis <em>Mastio</em></h3>
          <p class="cc-body">
            The authority that governs agents inside a single
            organization. Issues certificates, enforces policy, keeps
            a local hash-chain audit that never leaves the perimeter.
          </p>
          <dl class="cc-spec">
            <dt>Runs on</dt><dd>your infrastructure</dd>
            <dt>Owned by</dt><dd>your org admin</dd>
            <dt>Does</dt><dd>CA · policy · audit · reverse-proxy</dd>
          </dl>
        </article>

        <article class="component-card reveal" data-delay="3">
          <div class="cc-number">03</div>
          <div class="cc-label">Cross-org</div>
          <h3 class="cc-title">Cullis <em>Court</em></h3>
          <p class="cc-body">
            Federates Mastios across different organizations. Routes
            sealed envelopes between companies — sees who and when,
            never sees what was said.
          </p>
          <dl class="cc-spec">
            <dt>Runs on</dt><dd>network operator's infrastructure</dd>
            <dt>Owned by</dt><dd>one company or a consortium</dd>
            <dt>Does</dt><dd>registry · federation · ciphertext routing</dd>
          </dl>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <!-- QUICKSTART -->
  <section class="prose-section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="eyebrow reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow-number">03</span>
        Quickstart
      </div>
      <h2 class="reveal" data-delay="1">
        One command to <em>federated</em>.
      </h2>
      <p class="reveal" data-delay="2">
        Boot the full enterprise stack — Court, two Mastios, three agents,
        two MCP servers across two organizations, wired with SPIRE,
        Keycloak, Vault and Postgres.
      </p>
      <pre class="reveal" data-delay="3"><code>git clone https://github.com/cullis-security/cullis
cd cullis
./sandbox/demo.sh full</code></pre>
      <p class="reveal" data-delay="4">
        Then replay intra-org MCP tool calls and cross-org A2A messages:
      </p>
      <pre class="reveal" data-delay="5"><code>./sandbox/demo.sh mcp-catalog     # intra-org: agent → MCP tool call (Org A)
./sandbox/demo.sh mcp-inventory   # intra-org: agent → MCP tool call (Org B)
./sandbox/demo.sh oneshot-a-to-b  # cross-org: encrypted A2A message A → B
./sandbox/demo.sh oneshot-b-to-a  # cross-org: encrypted A2A message B → A</code></pre>
      <p class="reveal note" data-delay="6">
        <strong>For single-user install</strong> — download the Cullis
        Connector from <a href="https://github.com/cullis-security/cullis/releases" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Releases</a> and double-click. It will register with a Mastio you point it at and configure
        your MCP client automatically.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <!-- CLOSING -->
  <section class="closing">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="closing-rule"></div>
      <div class="eyebrow reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow-number">04</span>
        Continue
      </div>
      <h2 class="reveal" data-delay="1">Architecture, <em>deployment</em>, components.</h2>
      <p class="reveal" data-delay="2">
        The rest lives on its own pages. Read about the two routing modes,
        the deployment shapes, and each component at length.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions reveal" data-delay="3">
        <a href="/architecture" class="btn btn-primary">Architecture</a>
        <a href="/deployment" class="btn btn-ghost">Deployment</a>
        <a href="/components" class="btn btn-ghost">Components</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding-top: clamp(6rem, 12vw, 9rem);
    padding-bottom: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 5rem);
  }

  .hero-container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(170px, 0.7fr) minmax(0, 3fr);
    gap: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 4rem);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .hero-marginalia {
    position: sticky;
    top: 7rem;
    padding-right: 1rem;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .hero-main {
    padding-top: 0.3rem;
  }

  .hero-title {
    margin: 0 0 1.8rem 0;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .hero-lead {
    font-size: clamp(1.02rem, 1.45vw, 1.18rem);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0 0 2.2rem 0;
    max-width: 56ch;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .hero-stats {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 1.5rem 0 0 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    max-width: 560px;
  }

  .hero-stats div {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.3rem;
  }

  .hero-stats dt {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
  }

  .hero-stats dd {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .hero-stats dd em {
    color: var(--accent-cyan);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .hero-seal {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    color: var(--accent-cyan);
    padding-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .hero-seal svg {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 230px;
    height: auto;
    color: var(--accent-cyan);
    animation: sealBreath 7s ease-in-out infinite;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 16px rgba(0, 229, 199, 0.18));
  }

  @keyframes sealBreath {
    0%, 100% { transform: scale(1); opacity: 1; }
    50% { transform: scale(1.015); opacity: 0.92; }
  }

  .seal-caption {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.2rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    text-align: center;
  }

  /* Prose */
  .prose-section { padding: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 6rem) 0; }

  .prose-section h2 { margin-bottom: 2rem; }

  .prose-section p {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1.5em;
  }

  .prose-section p.note {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-cyan);
    background: var(--bg-card);
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .prose-section p.note strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  /* Components */
  .components-section { padding: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 6rem) 0; }

  .section-head {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .section-lead {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .components-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .component-card {
    padding: 2.2rem 1.75rem;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    position: relative;
    transition: transform 0.35s ease, border-color 0.35s ease, box-shadow 0.35s ease;
  }

  .component-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    border-color: var(--border-medium);
    box-shadow: 0 20px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3), 0 0 40px var(--accent-cyan-glow);
  }

  .cc-number {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 3rem;
    color: var(--accent-cyan);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  .cc-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.66rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .cc-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem 0;
    line-height: 1.15;
    padding-bottom: 1.25rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .cc-title em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent-cyan);
  }

  .cc-body {
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    max-width: none;
  }

  .cc-spec {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: 0.4rem 1rem;
    font-size: 0.86rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px dashed var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .cc-spec dt {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.64rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    padding-top: 0.2rem;
  }

  .cc-spec dd {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  /* Closing */
  .closing { padding: clamp(4rem, 8vw, 7rem) 0; }

  .closing-rule {
    width: 40px;
    height: 2px;
    background: var(--accent-cyan);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .closing h2 { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .closing p {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .hero-container {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }
    .hero-marginalia {
      position: static;
      padding-right: 0;
      padding-bottom: 1rem;
      border-right: none;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    }
    .hero-seal {
      order: -1;
      padding-top: 0;
    }
    .hero-seal svg { max-width: 150px; }
    .hero-stats { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .components-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
